snippet: A draft bill to wind down government-run mortgage financiers Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, released by two leading U.S. senators on Sunday, would leave a decision on how to treat their private shareholders to the courts....

headline.print_headline: Fannie, Freddie Bill Leaves Status of Private Shareholders to Courts
headline.main: Fannie, Freddie Bill Leaves Status of Private Shareholders to Courts

lead_paragraph: A draft bill to wind down government-run mortgage financiers Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, released by two leading U.S. senators on Sunday, would leave a decision on how to treat their private shareholders to the courts.
